Project Name: Minasian (Caro) Collection of Persian and Arabic Manuscripts
Title: Majmūʿah
Description.tableOfContents: Title: Risālah fī Baqāʾ al-nafs; A philosophical treatise on the immortality of the soul.|~|Title: Risālat al-wujūd; A philosophical treatise on the concept of being.|~|Title: Min Futūḥ al-ghayb; A one page theological fragment on being unjust to oneself and others.|~|Title: Min Man lā-yaḥḍuruhu al-faqīh|~|Title: al-Risālah al-naṣīriyah; A philosophical treatise on moral virtues and how to resist desires.|~|Title: Qiṭaʿ mutafarraqah; A collection of fragments in prose and verse on the lives of mystics and their virtues. Author is unknown.|~|Title: Mawʿiẓah balīghah li-arbaʿīn sūrah min al-Tawrāt; A commentary and theological analysis on forty verses in the Torah.|~|Title: Fī tafsīr al-Fātiḥah; A theological treatise on the concept of the grace of God in the Surat al-Fātiḥah.|~|Title: Ḥadīth ʿan Jālīnūs; A fragment of a moral story attributed to Jalinus (Galen).|~|Title: Arbaʿūn ḥadīthā; A ḥadith concerning the moral conduct and virtues of Muslims. Missing end folios.|~|Title: Hadīth ʿan Kumayl; A fragment of a ḥadīth attributed to Iṃām ʿAlī transmitted by Kumayl on the nature of the soul.|~|Title: Tārīkh-i madīnah-ʾi Sahmūdī; A Persian treatise on some important events that happened in the city of Sahmūdī in Iran. Author is unknown.|~|Title: Min Rawḍ al-rayāḥīn; A fragment of stories concerning the devotion and moral conduct of Muslims. Author is unknown.|~|Title: Min Kitāb al-imāmah wa al-siyāsah; Fragments from Ibn Qutaybah's al-Iṃāmah wa al-Sīỵāsah on the history of governance in Islamic empires.|~|Title: Shiʿr-i Fārsī; Poetic fragments in Persian. Author is unknown.|~|Title: Zahr al-akmām; A fragment from al-Anṣārī's Zahr al-akmām. It is a commentary on Surat Yūsuf in the Qurʾān.|~|Title: Zahr al-akmam; A fragment from Ghazzālī's Iḥyaʾ ʿulūm al-dīn, on asceticism and yearning for God.|~|Title: Min Ahādith al-Nabī; Some ḥādīths on asceticism, zuhd, in wordly life. Compiler is unknown.|~|Title: Fī musāwāt zawāyā al-muthallith; A fragment attributed to al-Fārābī on geometrical proof.|~|Title: Ḥadīth ʿan al-ṣādiq; A ḥadīth attributed to Jaʿfar al-Ṣādiq on the virtues of the prophet Muḥammad.|~|Title: Sharḥ muṣṭalaḥāt al-ṣūfīyah; A fragment dealing with explanations of mystical terminology. Author is unknown.

Source: Caro Minasian Collection of Persian and Arabic Manuscripts, box 46, 307
Description.abstract: Dānish'pazhūh claims that this manuscript is a collected work with two items. However, only the Kulliyāt of Shāpūr is present. For verification, Shāpūr's takhalus appears throughout the manuscript.
